claim.claim-text:
1. An isolated nucleic acid molecule comprising:
a) a nucleotide sequence as set forth in FIG. 2A (SEQ ID NO: 6);
b) a nucleotide sequence encoding a polypeptide as set forth in FIG. 2A (SEQ ID NO. 7) from residues 1-322 or from residues 47-322;
c) a nucleotide sequence of (b) encoding a polypeptide fragment of at least about 100 amino acid residues of SEQ ID NO: 7, wherein the polypeptide fragment has at least one activity selected from stimulating T-cell proliferation, activating T-cells, or binding to CRP1 of SEQ ID NO: 2; or
d) a nucleotide sequence fully complementary to any of (a), (b), or (c).

2. An isolated nucleic acid molecule comprising:
a) a nucleotide sequence as set forth in FIG. 12A (SEQ ID NO:16);
b) a nucleotide sequence as set forth in FIG. 12A (SEQ ID NO: 16) from nucleotides 1 to 909 inclusive;
c) a nucleotide sequence encoding a polypeptide as set forth in FIG. 12A (SEQ ID NO: 17) from residues 1-302, or from about residues 19-302, 20-302, 21-302, 22-302, 24-302, or 28-302, wherein the polypeptide has at least one activity selected from stimulating T-cell proliferation, activating T-cells, or binding to CRP1 of SEQ ID NO:22; or
d) a nucleotide sequence fully complementary to any of (a), (b) or (c).
